# Block Editor / Render Parity

- Editor (`edit.js`) and front-end (`render.php`) must look 100% the same while building and on output.
- Put Tailwind classes directly in `edit.js` and `render.php` side by side — do not route through shared constants unless the same class string is reused across multiple blocks in both JS and PHP.
- Child-only blocks (for example `mbn-column`) render their own markup directly; do not use `LayoutShellEdit` or `mbn_theme_render_layout_shell()`.
- Layout shell blocks (section, container, columns, gallery) use `LayoutShellEdit` in the editor and `mbn_theme_render_layout_shell()` in `render.php` with matching wrapper and content classes inlined in each block file.
- Use `get_block_wrapper_attributes()` on the outer wrapper in `render.php`; use `useBlockProps()` with the same `className` in `edit.js`.
- Keep DOM structure aligned: same wrapper classes, same nesting depth, no editor-only borders or padding unless required for block selection UI.
- Use `ob_start()` in `render.php`; do not concatenate HTML strings.
- Escape all render output; use `wp_kses_post()` only for trusted rich text.
- Dynamic blocks use `save: () => null` or `InnerBlocks.Content` as appropriate; enqueue via `block.json`, not inline scripts.

## Shared code scope

- No shared Tailwind class maps or class-name constants. Put classes directly in each block's `edit.js` and `render.php`.
- `layout-helpers.js` — editor logic only (inline styles, element id, scoped CSS). No class strings.
- `Mbn_Theme_Block_Layout` — PHP render logic only (`render_layout_shell`, inline styles, scoped CSS). No class-name constants.
- Dynamic grid classes: duplicate the same `switch` in `mbn-columns` and `mbn-gallery` `edit.js` + `render.php` with a `keep in sync` comment.
- After changing `blocks/*/render.php`, run `npm run build:blocks` so `build/blocks/` stays in sync (WordPress loads from `build/`).

## Example: classes inlined in both files

Child block `mbn-column`:

`edit.js`:
```javascript
const blockProps = useBlockProps( { className: 'mbn-column' } );
```

`render.php`:
```php
get_block_wrapper_attributes( array( 'class' => 'mbn-column' ) );
```

Shell block `mbn-container`:

`edit.js`:
```javascript
wrapperClassName="relative isolate min-h-px w-full overflow-hidden"
contentClassName="relative z-10 container mx-auto"
```

`render.php`:
```php
mbn_theme_render_layout_shell(
  $attributes,
  $content,
  'mbn-container',
  'relative isolate min-h-px w-full overflow-hidden',
  'relative z-10 container mx-auto'
);
```
